<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1484,1835]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,450,1520,1547]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">Original description:</emphasis>
“more elongated ovoid aperture; chamferings less deep; reddish yellow color with horny lustre”—with respect to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Muller, 1774)" authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1774" baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[426,797,1557,1583]" class="Gastropoda" family="Valvatidae" genus="Valvata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="piscinalis">
<emphasis box="[426,624,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">Valvata piscinalis</emphasis>
(Müller, 1774)
</taxonomicName>
, reported as 
<taxonomicName authority="Muller." authorityName="Muller." authorityYear="1774" box="[939,1227,1557,1583]" class="Gastropoda" family="Valvatidae" genus="Valvata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="piscinalis">
<emphasis box="[939,1137,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">Valvata piscinalis</emphasis>
Müller.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="363" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1484,1835]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1593,1619]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">Remarks:</emphasis>
having been instituted as a geographic race, we rank it subspecific, and thus available (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[1298,1432,1593,1619]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 10, glossary). Reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fasulo, G." box="[513,671,1629,1655]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="1 - 3" refId="ref17022" refString="Fasulo, G. (2013) Molluschi extramarini (terrestri e dulciacquicoli) &quot; campani &quot; per toponimia. Notiziario S. I. M., 31 (2), 1 - 3." type="journal article" year="2013">Fasulo (2013)</bibRefCitation>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Muller, 1774)" authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1774" baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[875,1252,1629,1655]" class="Gastropoda" family="Valvatidae" genus="Valvata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="piscinalis">
<emphasis box="[875,1075,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">Valvata piscinalis</emphasis>
(Müller, 1774)
</taxonomicName>
. This taxon was not figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[322,488,1665,1691]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="33 - 44" refId="ref15711" refString="Bellini, R. (1904 d) The freshwater shells of Naples and the neighbourhood. Journal of Conchology, 11 (2), 33 - 44." type="journal article" year="1904">Bellini (1904d</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[501,561,1664,1691]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="149 - 194" refId="ref15792" refString="Bellini, R. (1915) I molluschi extramarini dei dintorni di Napoli. Monografia sintetica. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, Series 2, 27, 149 - 194." type="journal article" year="1915">1915</bibRefCitation>
); however, taking into account the absence of congeneric and/or similar species from the Naples area (
<bibRefCitation author="Welter-Schultes, F." box="[449,696,1701,1727]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" refId="ref19699" refString="Welter-Schultes, F. (2012) European non-marine molluscs, a guide for species identification. Planet Poster Editions, Gottingen, 680 pp." type="book" year="2012">Welter-Schultes 2012</bibRefCitation>
), as well as the fact that it is generally a very common species, we are prone to accept that it was truly described as based on 
<taxonomicName authority="O.F.Muller, 1774" authorityName="O.F.Muller" authorityYear="1774" baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[803,937,1737,1763]" class="Gastropoda" family="Valvatidae" genus="Valvata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="piscinalis">
<emphasis box="[803,937,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="363">V. piscinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This taxon was not found during samplings held in the area in the 1980’s (
<bibRefCitation author="Battaglini, P. &amp; Valentino, M. G." box="[494,813,1773,1799]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" pagination="233 - 259" refId="ref15554" refString="Battaglini, P. &amp; Valentino, M. G. (1981 - 1982) Aspetti ecologici di un fiume urbano ad alta alterazione ambientale (Fiume Sebeto). Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, 90 - 91, 233 - 259." type="book chapter" year="1981">
Battaglini &amp; Valentino 
<date box="[757,813,1773,1799]" pageId="20" pageNumber="363" value="1981" valueMax="1982">1981</date>
</bibRefCitation>
–1982), and therefore it presumably did not survive the anthropogenic changes to which the Sebeto River has been subjected in the last century.
</paragraph>
